F. R. CRUIKSHANK & COMPANY OF THE PACIFIC, Appellant, v. CALIFORNIA CANNERIES COMPANY, Appellee. No. 8132. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 22, 1936. Pillsbury, Madison & Sutro, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Norman A. Eisner, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, each party to bear its own costs; mandate forthwith.
